'''shakuhachi'''<br>
'''灏哄叓'''

====Etymology====
Borrowed from Japanese ''shakuhachi'' 灏哄叓, from ''shaku'' (an archaic measure of length approximately equal to 30 centimeters) + ''hachi'', meaning "eight."

====Meaning====
A Japanese flute which is tuned to a [[pentatonic]] scale is end-blown like a recorder instead of being held transversely like the Western transverse flute, originally used by Zen Buddhist Monks in the practice of blowing meditation ([[Suizen]]).